        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"adaptation_kind\":\"Restructure\",\"safety_tier\":\"Green\",\"nudge_patch\":null,\"restructure_plan\":{\"revised_weekly_targets\":[{\"week_number\":1,\"weekly_target_km\":30},{\"week_number\":2,\"weekly_target_km\":34},{\"week_number\":3,\"weekly_target_km\":38}],\"revised_current_week_workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":1,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":7,\"target_duration_minutes\":42,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start very relaxed, let the body wake up gradually.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":32,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Comfortable conversational effort throughout.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Slow to a comfortable walk for the final minute.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Ease into the first 5 minutes; no pressure to hit pace immediately.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Finish with 5 minutes of light stretching, focusing on calves and hips.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This run stays as planned — you completed it well and it sets the aerobic foundation for the week. Keep effort genuinely easy; you should be able to hold a full conversation.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Recovery Run\",\"target_distance_km\":6,\"target_duration_minutes\":36,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start gently, no rush.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":26,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Purely aerobic, conversational pace throughout.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":380,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Wind down smoothly.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Start with a slow 5-minute walk or very light jog.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"End with gentle leg swings and calf stretches.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"The tempo session has been swapped for an easy run this week. Fatigue signals from your recent logs suggest your body will adapt better with aerobic volume rather than intensity right now. Keep this genuinely easy — if it feels too comfortable, that's exactly right.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":6,\"target_duration_minutes\":36,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Ease in gently.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":26,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady comfortable effort.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":380,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Gradual slow-down.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Take the first kilometre as a warm-up, running even more gently than target pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Finish with light stretching, especially hips and quads.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This run stays at its prescribed distance. Keep it easy and focus on how your legs feel compared to earlier in the week — noticing improving freshness is a good sign the body is responding well.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Reduced Long Run\",\"target_distance_km\":11,\"target_duration_minutes\":66,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start very easy, settle into rhythm.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":50,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady aerobic effort; back off immediately if legs feel heavy.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":380,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Bring the pace right down for the final 8 minutes.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Begin with a 5-minute walk then ease into easy running pace over the first kilometre.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk the final 2 minutes and follow with 10 minutes of full-body stretching.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"The long run target has been reduced from 14 km to 11 km this week. The goal is to complete this comfortably rather than push through fatigue. If legs feel heavy again, it is absolutely fine to stop at 9–10 km — a controlled easy long run at this stage is far more valuable than grinding through.\",\"perceived_effort\":5}],\"forward_path\":\"Week 2 steps back up to 34 km with the tempo session returning on Wednesday, but at a shorter 6 km version to let your legs rediscover that intensity without overwhelming them. Week 3 builds to 38 km with the full tempo and long run reinstated. If Week 2's tempo feels strong, Week 3 can nudge a little closer to the original 48 km target — but we'll let the data from your sessions guide that rather than committing to it now. The sub-1:45 goal remains well within reach; the plan simply needs a brief recalibration week to let your legs catch up with the ambition.\"},\"net_load_delta\":-10,\"rationale\":\"Cutting a long run short when your legs just aren't there is a smart, honest move — well done for listening to your body rather than grinding through. Looking across the last three sessions, a consistent pattern stands out: your tempo pace ran noticeably slower than the Daniels-Gilbert zone target, your easy run took longer than planned, and the long run ended early with heavy legs rather than tired breathing. That picture points to accumulated fatigue rather than fitness loss — your aerobic engine (breathing was fine) is intact, but your legs need a little more time to recover and consolidate before absorbing more load. Here's what I've changed: this week's tempo has been replaced with a second easy run, and Sunday's long run is set at 11 km instead of 14 km, bringing the week's total to 30 km. That gives your legs the recovery space they're asking for without losing your aerobic base. Looking ahead, Week 2 steps back up to 34 km with a shorter tempo session returning, and Week 3 rebuilds to 38 km with full sessions reinstated. The sub-1:45 goal is still very much on the table — one recalibration week at this stage is an investment in the 15 weeks that follow.\",\"referral_category\":null}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
